title: Cìr Mhòr
text: Cìr Mhòr (<a href="Scottish%20Gaelic">Scottish Gaelic</a>, usually with <a href="definite%20article">definite article</a>, "A' Chìr Mhòr") is a <a href="Hill%20lists%20in%20the%20British%20Isles%23Corbetts">Corbett</a> known as the <a href="Matterhorn">Matterhorn</a> of <a href="Isle%20of%20Arran">Arran</a>. Its name means the "big comb", referring its resemblance to a <a href="Comb%20%28anatomy%29">cockscomb</a>. It is separated from the island's highest peak, <a href="Goat%20Fell">Goat Fell</a>, by a <a href="mountain%20pass">col</a> called "The Saddle".
